==Finnish==
===Noun===

halvattu (genitive/intensifier ''halvatun'', illative ''halvattuun'', inessive ''halvatussa'')

(mediocre expletive or intensifier) hell, fuck shit.

Finnish synonyms: [[helvetti]], [[hitto]]

===Examples===

* Plain: ''Kuka halvattu on puhkonut autoni renkaat?'' Who the hell has punctured my car tyres?
* Illative: ''Mihin halvattuun mä olen pudottanut avaimeni?'' Where the hell have I dropped my keys?
* Inessive: ''Missä halvatussa mun lmpakkoni on?'' Where the hell is my wallet?
* Intensifier: ''Se halvatun persläpi on syypää kaikkeen.'' That fucking asshole is the culprit for it all.

===Etymology===

Halvattu is a corrupt of [[helvetti]] and it sounds much like ''halvaantunut'', [[paralyze]]d. This can have a connection to old religious beliefs that disablilities are punishments for sin.